TY  - JOUR
AU  - Lin, Chunmei
AU  - Massa, Massimo
AU  - Zhang, Hong
T1  - Mutual Funds and Information Diffusion: The Role of Country-Level Governance
PY  - 2014
Y1  - 2014/11/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhu046
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 27
IS  - 11
SP  - 3343
EP  - 3387
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We hypothesize that poor country-level governance, which makes public information less reliable, induces fund managers to increase their use of semipublic information. Utilizing data from international mutual funds and stocks over the 2000–2009 period, we find that semipublic information-related stock rebalancing can be five times higher in countries with the worst quality of governance than in countries with the best. The use of semipublic information increases price informativeness but also increases information asymmetry and reduces stock liquidity. It also intensified the price impact and liquidity crunch during the recent global financial crisis.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhu046
ER  - 



